<br>
Take a look at Elemental Pact... <br>
Class skill: Required lvl 59<br>
- By lvl 59 the majority of Magician's have their epic and rarely ever use any other pet.  <br>
<br>
This would be a much better skill at lvl 55 or when you can spend points on Archetype Skills.  How would Verant do this? No idea, but it's simply not useful at 59 or 60.<br>
<br>
<br>
Improved Reclaim Energy<br>
Class skill: Required lvl 59<br>
-By lvl 59 to 60 most mages don't bother with Reclaim Energy, even fewer waste mana chain casting Pets, and also realize that Modding will be much more efficient then casting pets just to get mana.  By the time most mages get this they've spent AA in SCM and have some type of mana conservation item, so Modding &gt; Reclaiming.  (Don't forget that a lot of them have SoAs)<br>
<br>
Yes their are exceptions to everything I have and will write.  But *most* mages don't solo OFTEN enough for this to be a useful skill or worth the points.<br>
<br>
<br>
Elemental form: Fire<br>
Class skill: Required lvl 59<br>
- Now this gives +FR, +int and a DS...  This isn't really useful at lvl 59 either for a few reasons:  1) At lvl 59-60 mages have normally been around long enough to aquire enough 'good' gear to be at or near max int with KEI.  2) Having a extra DS on yourself won't do any good because your pet is the one getting hit not you.  3) Additional saves become meaningless because Air Elemental form gives you more/better saves<br>
<br>
This form would be more useful at lvl 55 as well when the mage is first starting to establish themselves in a guild and aquire better equipement through lvling/raiding.  *OR* it could be made more useful at lvl 59-60 by giving Mana instead of Intelligence.  Give a set amount of mana or do it by percent like 2%, 4%, 8%. (8% being the total not 2 + 4 + 8.)   And instead of giving you a iniate DS, allow it to add  +1, +3, +5pts of dmg to DS you cast on another player... then have the +FR as an additional, probably useless, thing.<br>
<br>
Elemental form: Water<br>
Class skill: Required lvl 59<br>
- This form is just silly.  18pts for 3 (or is it 4) mana per tick.  I honestly don't think it's useful at any lvl unless the cost is dropped on it.  <br>
<br>
Maybe no steps just a 9pt Form, you either have it or you don't.  If it's impossible to change because players already have it and refunding points would be a pain... buff it up a little...  2mana/hps, 4mana/hps, and then 6mana/hps per tick for the 3rd form. (6hps/mana total)  <br>
<br>
Elemental form: Earth<br>
Class skill: Required lvl 59<br>
- Gives additional Sta/hps etc etc...<br>
<br>
This form isn't useful at all... it needs something else.  Now that we get ND, we can get about the same amount of hps by getting ND3 as we do for getting Earth form to lvl 3, for 12 pts instead of 18.  Even if we didn't get ND, just the additional Sta/HP's isn't enough to spend 18pts for.<br>
<br>
Take a look at the &quot;Improved&quot; familar that wizzies get before you say any of this is to over powered.  For their points, they get 6mana/tick, 250 mana + 30sv all for 9pts (Or something very close to that, I don't remember EXACTLY what they get.)  They get ALL of that in their 9pts.  We have 3 forms at 18pts a piece that aren't close to that in any way.<br>
<br>
Mass Group Buff = a way to piss off your guild Rangers, but otherwise useless.<br>
<br>
Mend Companion is *ok* but sub-par if you compare our AA abilities to another class.  And totally useless if you're grouping, the tank should be taking dmg not the pet.<br>
<br>
Frenized Burnout is useless but always neat to watch your pet flurry/rampage. ^.^  Especially in a raid or around &quot;newbie&quot; zones.<br>
<br>
Turned Summon.... Totally useful for all those creatures tagged *summoned* in every zone (/sarcasam off).  I haven't been to the Hole since... I don't remember<br>
<br>
Pet Discipline and Quick Summoning are the only two AA's that I believe would be good post 59 Class AA.  Even tho pet's don't attack mezzed creatures, Pet Disc does still help from time to time.<br>
<br>
So my point to ALL of this is, it's not that our AA are totally are useless.  It's that they just aren't useful at the lvl you get them.  There is nothing to make you WANT to go out and spend time xping.  To other classes, the final AApts they have access to are their class defining skills.  To mages it's just a little to late.  We don't need totally new AA's, though it probably wouldn't hurt, they just need to be improved.<br>
<br>
