<br>
 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Elemental Pact</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: This looks to be the mage equivalent to ranger's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> endless quiver</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. The only exception is that rangers have to spend 9 points to get their skill while mages only have to spend 5. Rangers definitly get more of a benefit from this since there are some pretty powerful arrows in the game, and malachite never changes in how effective it is. Overall, the reason that I bought this skill is cause its worth 5 points to me to never have to worry about carrying malachite (along with saving all the bag space). <br>
<br>
  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Improved Reclaim</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->Used alone, this skill isn't incredibly impressive. But, when combined with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SCM3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> QS2</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->( along with the casting time focus ring), this skill appears to lead to some pretty impressive mana regen ability. <br>
<br>
  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Elemental form:Fire</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Interesting skill to have. but outside of pvp, I really cannot find alot of use for it. <br>
<br>
  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Mend Companion</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> To me, this isn't a skill that I want to use all the time. Its an emergency skill to be used when pet is about to die, and the mage is going to be close behind. <br>
<br>
  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Turn Summoned</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Unless you pvp alot, its a pretty useless skill. I was slightly miffed when they changed the skill from casting <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> rebuke summoned lvl1</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to lvl2 as it gave this skill too long of a casting time to be truly effective in pvp<br>
<br>
  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> frenzied burnout</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> this skill isn't useless, its broken.<br>
<br>
  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Pet hold</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> arguably the best class skill that mages get. Although with the recent pet changes, its made this skill nowhere near as incredible as it used to be, its still very nice to have. <br>
